Mario &amp; Luigi: Superstar Saga, known in Japan as Mario &amp; Luigi RPG (マリオ＆ルイージRPG, Mario ando Ruīji Ārupījī), is a role-playing game developed by AlphaDream and published by Nintendo for the Game Boy Advance in 2003.
Unique to Mario &amp; Luigi: Superstar Saga is the Bros. Moves, which becomes available after new abilities are gained.
The playable protagonists in the game are Mario and Luigi.
